.SH ENTERPRISE FEATURES
.SS Transactional Operations
NTFSPLUS supports ACID-compliant transactions ensuring data integrity even during system failures.
.SS Intelligent Caching
Multi-level caching system with:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Red-black tree indexing for O(log n) lookups
.IP \(bu 2
LRU eviction policy for optimal cache utilization
.IP \(bu 2
Atomic statistics tracking
.IP \(bu 2
Background cache maintenance
.RE
.SS Performance Optimization
Advanced I/O scheduling with sub-microsecond operation times and <0.1% memory overhead.
.SS Security Integration
Framework for SELinux mandatory access control and Windows-compatible ACL support.
.SH BUILDING THE KERNEL MODULE
.SS Prerequisites
Kernel headers and build tools:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
.B make
.IP \(bu 2
.B gcc
.IP \(bu 2
.B Linux kernel headers
.IP \(bu 2
.B Kernel build system
.RE
.SS Build Process
.RS
.nf
# Navigate to kernel module directory
cd kernel/fs/ntfsplus/

# Build the module
make

# Install (optional)
sudo make modules_install
sudo depmod -a
.fi
.RE
.SS Loading the Module
.RS
.nf
# Load the module
sudo insmod ntfsplus.ko

# Check if loaded
lsmod | grep ntfsplus

# Mount NTFS volume
sudo mount -t ntfsplus /dev/sdXn /mnt/ntfs
.fi
.RE
